de.boereck.matcher.helpers

Class LongMatchHelpers

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.boereck.matcher.helpers.LongMatchHelpers

  • public final class LongMatchHelpers
extends Object
    This class provides static methods and final fields holding references to methods that can be used as predicates in case definitions of matchers for long values. This class is not intended to be instantiated or sub-classed.

      • inClosedRange

        public static AdvLongPredicate inClosedRange(long startIncluding,
                                             long endIncluding)
                                      throws IllegalArgumentException
        Returns a predicate that checks if an input long is in the closed range from startIncluding to endIncluding.
        Parameters:
        startIncluding - start value. Input may be greater or equal to this.
        endIncluding - end value. Input may be lower or equal to this.
        Returns:
        predicate checking if an input value is in the closed range from startIncluding to endIncluding.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if startIncluding > endIncluding.

      • allExcept

        public static AdvLongPredicate allExcept(long excluding,
                                         long... excludingMore)
                                  throws NullPointerException
        Returns a predicate that checks if a given long value is not on a black list of long values, defined by parameters excluding and excludingMore.
        Parameters:
        excluding - if input value to returned predicate equals this value, the predicate will return false
        excludingMore - excluding if input value to returned predicate equals any of this int values, the predicate will return false. This parameter must not be null, but may be an empty array.
        Returns:
        Predicate that returns false if the input value equals excluding or values in excludingMore, otherwise it returns true.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if excludingMore is null.
